{
  "stem": "5810.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And what he did, he built behind the wall of the attic, a-- he put up a false wall-- a wooden, for lack of a better word right now, let's call it paneling with a space where you could lay down on the floor about two feet wide and about six feet long.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But only if one body laid on top of the other could you hide behind this thing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the best way to hide it was not to protrude it, so he had to take whatever space was left behind this wall, and build this false wall.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's was going to be our hiding place from then on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember the searches that came after where we were made to go up and be behind that wall.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this comes my second nightmare story is that I was laying on the floor, face down, and my mother on top of me face down.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the only thing that I saw, sometimes for hours, because it wasn't just the searches that, that made us stay there, we wanted to make sure it was safe hours after.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we stayed there sometimes for hours on end just laying flat, my mother on top of me and me just looking at this tile, which had the Fleur de lis.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it just escaped me later on as to why I always saw this pattern and I woke up in screaming and nightmares and so on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then to jump over, when I finally visited the Barniche way after the war, 25-30 years later, where the house was totally and completely untouched.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Barniche were still alive, and they took my wife and I, who had heard many stories about that but had never seen it, up to the attic.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
